Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of robots to model infant development, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of formal models based on mathematics and algorithms, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The concept of viewing development as a complex dynamical system suggests a potential fit with systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of robots to study the impact of changing the body on skill formation suggests a potential fit with neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
